HEADWORD: Ochlesis
<hw>Och*le"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/ disturbance, fr. <grk>'o`chlos</grk> crowd, mob.]</ety>
<fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A general morbid condition induced by the
crowding together of many persons, esp. sick persons, under one
roof.</def> <rj><au>G. Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

